<div class="sec-head"><span>An example of how the rules make everything better: Kpop</span></div>
<div class="content">
  <p>Kpop isn’t for fun. It’s a business. It’s not just 5, 6, 7, 8 — it’s 10. Always.</p>
  <p>Collectivist culture combined with a tacit agreement to ‘the rules’ creates an enjoyable climate of content that thrives on structure.</p>
  <div class="kpop-rules">
    <div class="kpop-rule"><div class="kpop-n">1</div><div class="kpop-text">The training system ensures participants (“idols”) meet set standards — you can trust they’ll be qualified for the job.</div></div>
    <div class="kpop-rule"><div class="kpop-n">2</div><div class="kpop-text">Groups are built in planned structures — deliberate roles and responsibilities means expectations are clear for both participants and viewers.</div></div>
